valueString:
IMPRESSION: (WHOLE BODY MRI)


1. Minimal increase in size of a left occipital scalp enhancing lesion, 
now measures 4.5 x 2.4 x 2.2 cm..


2. Multiple stable peripheral soft tissue masses in the head, neck, and 
chest, similar to previous examination in size and number, presumed 
peripheral nerve sheath tumors. These lesions are more numerous on the 
left side and overall the disease in this patient is upper body 
predominant.


3. Evaluation of the ADC map of the lesions described above does not 
demonstrate suspicious low ADC values. However, ADC mapping is limited 
due to artifact.
